Juan Alvarez was sentenced to 11 consecutive life terms by Judge William Pounders, Superior Court of Los Angeles, CA.
The judge said he would have imposed a sentence of ''forever'' if it was possible.
The jury foreman said at a news conference, after the trial he did not believe Alvarez planned to kill anyone.
Alvarez’s attorneys intend to appeal the conviction on the basis Alvarez did not intend to kill anyone.
